5:42 was my situation, let’s say, 5 months ago. I’m a boy and I’m bi. This boy I liked was very... touchy. He always put his arm around my shoulder, and simple gestures like that. I was also told by someone that he was bi too. Also awesome. I don’t know what came over me, but I decided to text him this LONG paragraph of a message about how I liked him, nothing too mushy, just something short and to the point. This was the point that everything went way downhill. I didn’t get anything back for a month. I saw him everyday at school, but he started to ignore me. This caused me to go into a huge anxiety attack. I was ranting to my cousin, who is literally my partner in crime, who lives out of state. I sent her his instagram, and then things got even more out of hand. She sent him a dm about how if he’s bi he should just come out and everything will be fine. I was getting texts from friends I had told who also knew him, ask what was going on, and it was chaos. The last part in this story, I texted him, told him that the message was my cousin. I finally got the reply I should have gotten in the first place. Turns out he was never bi, he was very straight and then I pretty much stopped talking to him. It sucks, and of course I still like him. But this was awhile ago. I carry on. This just really reminded me of it and I thought I’d share, thank you whoever you are, scrolling by :)

I don’t have a video but I have a YouTube comment I guess??
(btw both of us are 14) 

So my closest friend, Katherine, and I are very lovey friends and we especially enjoy each other’s company. For me, I thought I was the only person in our relationship that had any romantic attraction to the other person and I was very certain of it. She, for awhile, did this thing where she would have a code name for her crush, the biggest one being code named “David Hasselhoff.” SO, one day, while Katherine was on a weekend long Model UN trip, I asked another friend of mine, MeiLi, also in Model UN and sharing a room with her, over FaceTime who this David Hasselhoff was. She came back with the question “would it be weird for your friend were to have a crush on you?” 

     I said no because this had occurred before and I never like making people uncomfortable and don’t want their attraction to me to affect our relationship in any way negatively. By that one question, I kinda got the gist of who this mystery person that she wouldn’t tell me about was. Me, of course. 

I was really excited but kinda scared that things would be awkward, which caused her to kinda avoid me the next day because she thought she would make me uncomfortable. Me, being a softy, went home, and texted with MeiLi about how much I really truly liked Katherine, to a point where I got so stressed about her being uncomfortable that I cried like a baby, because I’m just a baby in a teenage girl body.

I, in that same night, told her “Did you ever consider the fact that David Hasselhoff might like you too?” and then got up and ran around my house waiting for a response. She said she was relieved that her having a crush on me wouldn’t make me uncomfortable, and we just became closer because of it. That was about a week or so ago, and we said we would get over each other together, but at this point I don’t know if I want to get over her. I want to go out on a date with her and be with her all the time and cuddle with her like we do all the time but in a different context. I don’t want to tell her and overwhelm her with that but I want her to know. I truly do love her, and she is the best human that has ever come into my life.

Everyone ships us but we choose not to feed them what they want. The ship name is Kemma, which is pretty lame but I like it because Katherine likes it.

- From a weird teenage girl

MIKEY I need your help..... I like a guy, and we have a class together, but there's an... "interference," of sorts. When I am in a class with the guy I used to like, I get "feelings" for him, like I like him, but when I am not around him I don't feel that way. I feel the same about the guy I currently like at all times though. I often think about writing them notes, for example: *Dear (old crush), I used to like you. But as I grew, I came to my senses and realized there was someone else who was trying so hard to break a barrier I was oblivious to between us. I want to let you go, but every time I'm around you I can't shake the feeling that I still like you. If you did or do like me, write back. If not, I can live with that. It might not put my heart at ease, but I will know something. From, (myself).* But then I enter the classes I have with him and I feel like ripping it up and throwing it away. If I were to write a note to the guy I like now, I would say something like: *Dear (current crush), I have told myself I would tell you in person, but I see I'm too wimpy to say it. Instead, I write. I like you. It's taken me a while to notice, and I've seen minor signs you like me. If this ruins our friendship and you don't, I didn't mean for it to end this way. I can't drag this weight around anymore. Do you like me? Y/N     From my whole heart, (myself).*

BUT I DON'T KNOW. I get... nervous?? around him and I can't bring myself to do it. This issue has delayed my sleep schedule and disrupted many thought trains. Help?
